  "prompt": "What is the legal history of money laundering prohibitions?",
  "response": "The legal history of money laundering prohibitions is complex and has evolved significantly over time. Here's an overview of key developments:\n\n1. Early Origins:\n- Concepts of concealing illicit financial gains date back centuries\n- Initial focus was primarily on criminal proceeds from activities like smuggling and tax evasion\n\n2. United States Developments:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (1970) - First major legislative effort to combat money laundering\n- Required financial institutions to report large currency transactions\n- Established reporting and record-keeping requirements\n\n3. International Milestones:\n- 1988 UN Vienna Convention - First international treaty addressing money laundering related to drug trafficking\n- Established framework for international cooperation against financial crimes\n- Encouraged countries to criminalize money laundering\n\n4. Global Regulatory Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) established in 1989\n- Developed comprehensive international standards for combating money laundering\n- Created recommendations for national legal and regulatory systems\n\n5. Post-9/11 Developments:\n- USA PATRIOT Act (2001) significantly expanded money laundering regulations\n- Enhanced international information sharing\n- Introduced stricter compliance requirements for financial institutions\n\n6. Ongoing Evolution:\n- Continuous adaptation to technological changes\n- Increased focus on cryptocurrency and digital financial transactions",
